{"key":"post-18584184","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>18584184</id>\n<content>That's what we call 'split' caps as opposed to 'cracked' caps.&amp;nbsp; Split caps are caused by growing too fast where the cells can't expand fast enough to hold all the water being pumped in.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Cracked caps more resemble the cracks on a turtle or horned toads back, and are caused by too low a humidity.&amp;nbsp; Cracked caps can actually improve food quality and are often deliberately produced with shiitake by subjecting them to a constantly fluctuating humidity between 10% and 90%.&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/13-29/433479745-Dried-White-Flower-Shiitake-Mushroom.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/13-29/433479745-thumb_Dried-White-Flower-Shiitake-Mushroom.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>18584306</next>\n<prev>18584124</prev>\n<first>18582702</first>\n<last>18598008</last>\n<when>1374334941</when>\n<utime>07/20/13 06:42 PM</utime>\n</post>"}